from time to time...

13
00:02:53,609 --> 00:02:57,284
...we have special guests,
and today, somebody truly special.

14
00:02:57,489 --> 00:03:01,004
Mr. Clayton Moore,
the Lone Ranger, right over here!

15
00:03:01,169 --> 00:03:03,558
And l've always wanted
to do this with you--

16
00:03:03,849 --> 00:03:08,161
-Hi-yo, Silver. Away!
-I never get tired of that.

17
00:03:08,329 --> 00:03:11,241
Do people recognize you
when you're out in public?

18
00:03:11,409 --> 00:03:12,888
No. No, not really.

19
00:03:13,089 --> 00:03:16,001
Can we get you to expose
yourself today on radio?

20
00:03:16,169 --> 00:03:19,605
-Mask off? Reveal your identity?
-For you, Bob, sure.

21
00:03:19,809 --> 00:03:23,722
Coming up next, a KNX first. We've
got the Lone Ranger, and he's naked!

22
00:03:24,369 --> 00:03:26,644
-Don't tell Tonto.
-No, of course not.

23
00:03:26,849 --> 00:03:30,319
First, a word from our sponsor,
Lucky Strike cigarettes.

24
00:03:42,769 --> 00:03:45,158
I always wanted
to make an impression.

25
00:03:45,329 --> 00:03:48,207
You know the type.
There's one in every class.

26
00:03:48,369 --> 00:03:52,999
The cutup. Eddie Cantor once told
me likeability is 90% of the battle...

27
00:03:53,169 --> 00:03:57,082
...and he was riaht.
